	<A CLASS="chapter" NAME="2.84">84</A>
Virgo delivered outside the City 200 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>. The remaining 2,304 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> were distributed within the City to the seventh, ninth, and fourteenth wards, among eighteen reservoirs. Of these there were furnished in the name of Caesar 509 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, to private parties 338 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, for public uses 1,167 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, — namely, to two ornamental fountains 26 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, to <SPAN CLASS="whole">twenty-five</SPAN> basins 51 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, to


<A ID="p415"><SPAN CLASS="pagenum"> p415 </SPAN></A>sixteen public structures&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" ID="ref118" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#note118
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">118</A> 1,380 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>. In the amount delivered to public structures are included 460 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> for the Euripus&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" ID="ref119" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#note119
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
