"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">47</A>
<I>i.e.</I>, how much under ground; how much on arches, etc.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note48" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref48
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">48</A>
<I>i.e.</I>, when old aqueducts were rebuilt, they were carried <I>across</I> valleys on arches or low foundations, instead of going <I>around</I> the valleys, as the original <SPAN CLASS="whole">under</SPAN>&shy;ground structures had done.


