	<P CLASS="halfstart justify">
He also uses <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Sescuncis</SPAN>, 1½ × <SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">1</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">12</SPAN></SPAN>, (or <SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">1</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">8</SPAN></SPAN>); <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Duella</SPAN>, <SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">1</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">36</SPAN></SPAN>; <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Sicilicus</SPAN>, <SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">1</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">48</SPAN></SPAN>; and <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Sextula</SPAN>, <SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">1</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">72</SPAN></SPAN>; and depends on combinations of these to express exact terms. Owing to corruptions in text, Frontinus's figures are often at variance with obvious facts.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note66" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref66
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">66</A>
Frontinus merely means that, instead of tapping the main conduit for individual consumers, the Romans delivered a given number of <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> to a reservoir, from which the water was delivered to the consumer.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note67" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref67
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">67</A>
It seems advisable to restate, for clearness' sake, the two principles of increase referred to by Frontinus. In the first class we have pipes, whose capacity is some multiple of the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinaria</SPAN>. In the second class, we have an ascending series of pipes each of which increases beyond the next smaller by a diameter of ¼ inch. In other words the first class is 


<A ID="p371x"></A>based on <I>multiples</I> of volume; the second on <I>slight increases</I> in diameters.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note68" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref68
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">68</A>
<I>i.e.</I> for the pipes above the 20‑pipe.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note69" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref69
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">69</A>
<I>i.e.</I> those mentioned in 28 and 29<!-- DON'T LINK -->.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note70" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref70
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">70</A>
By successive additions of a quarter of a digit to the diameter of a <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinaria</SPAN>, the diameter of the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">vicenaria</SPAN> becomes five digits or <I>twenty</I> quarter digits. The number of square digits in the cross section, therefore, would be π(<SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">5</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">2</SPAN></SPAN>)<SPAN CLASS="superscript">2</SPAN> = 19.6 (almost <I>twenty</I>) square digits.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note71" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref71
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">71</A>
Trajan is meant.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note72" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref72
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">72</A>
The water-men.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note73" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref73
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">73</A>
Frontinus's reckoning is as follows: The capacity of a 20‑pipe is 16<SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">7</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">24</SPAN></SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.46
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">46</A>); the capacity of the 100‑pipe is 81<SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">65</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">144</SPAN></SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.62
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">62</A>); the capacity of five 20‑pipes, therefore, practically equals that of one 100‑pipe. Now, if the gain resulting from <I>selling</I> by short measure was 3<SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">7</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">24</SPAN></SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> in one 20‑pipe, it will have been 16<SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">11</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">24</SPAN></SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> in five 20‑pipes (or one 100‑pipe). In the same way, since the capacity of the 120‑pipe is 97¾ <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.63
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">63</A>), it is equal to six 20‑pipes, and the gain in this case will he be 19¾ <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>. But by the increase of the pipes through which they <I>receive</I> water (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.32
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">32</A>), the gain was 10<SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">13</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">24</SPAN></SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> in case of the 100‑pipe, and 66⅙ <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> in case of the 120‑pipe; so that by adding the gains made at both ends of the bargain, we 


<A ID="p375x"></A>arrive at an aggregate gain of 27 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> in case of the 100‑pipe, and of 85<SPAN CLASS="fraction"><SPAN CLASS="top">11</SPAN>&frasl;<SPAN CLASS="bottom">12</SPAN></SPAN>, practically 86, <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> in case of the 120‑pipe.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note74" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref74
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">74</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.31
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">31</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note75" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref75
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">75</A>
Literally: "stops distributing, as though the ajutage had run dry." Whoever wished to draw water for private uses had to seek for a grant and bring to the water-commissioner a writing from the sovereign (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#2.103
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">103</A>,
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#2.105
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
105</A>). Now, the records show that Caesar's grants from a 100‑pipe amounted only to 81 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, and from a 120‑pipe to only 98 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, leaving a surplus to be accounted for.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note76" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref76
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">76</A>
The Roman pint.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note77" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref77
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">77</A>
About a gill.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note78" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref78
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">78</A>
The Roman peck.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note79" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref79
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">79</A>
<I>i.e.</I> to make the pipe discharge the normal quantity allotted to a pipe of that size.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note80" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref80
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">80</A>
<I>i.e.</I> in any particular instance.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note81" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref81
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">81</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.26
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">26 ff.
	</A>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note82" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref82
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">82</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.26
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">26</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note83" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref83
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">83</A>
Trajan, not Nerva, is meant. From the allusions in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#2.93
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chapter 93
	</A>
to Caesar Nerva Trajan Augustus, and in <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#2.102
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">102
	</A>
to Divus Nerva, it is concluded that this work which was begun under Nerva was finished under Trajan.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note84" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref84
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">84</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.31
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">31</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note85" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref85
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">85</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#note103
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">footnote to 74</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note86" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref86
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">86</A>
In this and several following paragraphs, Frontinus points out various discrepancies which existed in the accounting for the different water supplies. These are (1) the difference between the amount of water <I>found by actual measurement</I> to exist, and the amount <I>attributed</I> to each 


<A ID="p389x"></A>water supply <I>in the imperial records</I>; (2) the difference between the amount of water <I>recorded as received</I> and that <I>delivered</I>; (3) the difference between the amount <I>proved by measurement</I> and that <I>delivered</I>. In some cases, where the waters were received in catch-basins, or reservoirs (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.19
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">19</A>), he computes separately the amounts lost before the water reached the basin, and that lost afterwards.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note87" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref87
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">87</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.5
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">5</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note88" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref88
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">88</A>
The area of a cross section of the Appia would be 2,240 square digits (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.24
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">24</A>). The area of <SPAN CLASS="whole">twenty-two</SPAN> 100‑pipes would be 2,199 square digits (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.62
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">62</A>), and that of one 40‑pipe would be 39.98 square digits (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.50
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">50</A>), so that the area of a cross section of the Appia would practically equal 


<A ID="p391x"></A>the sum of the area of the cross sections of these pipes. Now the capacity of <SPAN CLASS="whole">twenty-two</SPAN> 100‑pipes, 1,791.93 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.62
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">62</A>), added to that of one 40‑pipe, 32.58 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.50
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">50</A>), gives approximately 1,825 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> as the capacity of the Appia at that point.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note89" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref89
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">89</A>
In the Appia (1) actual measurements showed 1,825 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, the records called for 841 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> — a discrepancy of 984 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>; (2) while the records credited 841 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, only 704 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> were delivered, a discrepancy of 137 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>; (3) 1,825 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> were found by measurement, but only 704 were delivered, a discrepancy of 1,121 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note90" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref90
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">90</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">6</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note91" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref91
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">91</A>
Old Anio was received into a catch-basin. (1) The measurements at the intake showed 4,389 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, the records credited 1,541 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, a discrepancy of 2,857 <A ID="p393x"></A></SPAN>quinariae</SPAN>; (2) between the intake and the reservoir 262 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> were distributed, and measurements at the reservoir showed 2,362 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, revealing a loss of 1,774 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> above the reservoir; (3) above and below the reservoir, there were delivered in all 1,610 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, 69 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> more than the records showed; but since measurements at the reservoir found 2,362 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, and only 1,348 were delivered below that, 1,014 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> remained unaccounted for, and the loss above and below the reservoir totalled 2,788 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note92" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref92
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">92</A>
Marcia was received into a catch-basin. In the following computations, Frontinus sometimes includes and sometimes disregards the amounts given to Tepula and Anio. (1) The measurements at the intake showed 4,690 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, the records credited 2,612 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, a discrepancy of 2,528 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>; (2) between the intake and the reservoir 351 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> were delivered (including those given to Tepula and Anio), and measurements at the reservoir showed 2,944 <A ID="p395x"></A><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, thus revealing a loss of 1,395 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> above the reservoir; (3) above and below the reservoir, there were delivered in all 95 plus 1,840 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> (this does <I>not</I> take account of the contributions to Tepula and Anio), 227 fewer <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> than the amount credited in the records; and the amount delivered below the reservoir was 1,104 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> less than the amount measured at the reservoir. Since the amount at the intake was 4,690 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, and the total distribution (including the amounts given to Tepula and Anio) amounted to 2,191 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, there remained 2,499 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> still unaccounted for.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note93" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref93
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">93</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.9
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">9</A>, <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.19
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">19</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note94" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref94
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">94</A>
That is, Tepula received and delivered 445 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, while the records credited only 400.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note95" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref95
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">95</A>
Julia was received into a catch-basin. (1) The measurements there taken showed its volume to be 1,206 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, 


<A ID="p397x"></A>while the records credited only 649 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, a discrepancy of 557 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>; (2) there were delivered in all 997 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, 344 more than were credited in the records, but 213 less than the gauges showed at the reservoir. (The 162 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> received from Claudia are not reckoned in computing this loss.)


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note96" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref96
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">96</A>
Claudia was received into a catch-basin. (1) The measurements at the intake showed 4,607 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, the records credited 2,855 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, a discrepancy of 1,752 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>; (2) measurements at the reservoir showed 3,312 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN>, a loss of 1,295 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> between the intake and 


<A ID="p401x"></A>the reservoir; (3) 1,750 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> were delivered, a smaller amount than that indicated by the records or by either set of measurements. (In the 1,750 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> were included the 162 given to Julia. <I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#2.69
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">69</A>.)


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note97" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref97
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">97</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.13
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">13, 14</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note98" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref98
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">98</A>
<I>i.e.</I> at the sources of the aqueduct.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note99" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref99
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
