<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.12
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">12</A>, <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.14
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">14</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note100" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref100
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">100</A>
The 4,200 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> included the 163 given to Tepula. <I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#2.68
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">68</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note101" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref101
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">101</A>
Literally: "the amount estimated by me even exceeds (the figures which I gave)."


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note102" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref102
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">102</A>
"The most troublesome point of ignorance which Frontinus had to contend with was a total inability to measure the velocity of water, or even rightly and fully to grasp the idea of such velocity, whether as flowing in an open channel or in closed pipes. He accordingly compares streams of water merely by the area of their cross sections, and then worries himself into all sorts of explanations as to why his gaugings by area, made irrespective of heads and velocities, do not balance. The frauds of the water-men, of the plumbers and of others who draw water unlawfully, always furnish a handy explanation, however." — <I>Herschel</I>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note103" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref103
