85‑48 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> See Cicero, <I>Epistulae ad Familiares</I>, <SPAN CLASS="small">VIII</SPAN>.6.4 (c. 50 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note105" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref105
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">105</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.20
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">20</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note106" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref106
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">106</A>
Since Frontinus in 87 speaks of the rebuilding of Marcia under Trajan, it is probable that after Claudia was brought to this quarter, the aqueducts previously supplying it were allowed to fall into disuse.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note107" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref107
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">107</A>
<I>i.e.</I> by discovering and correcting frauds.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note108" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref108
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">108</A>
<I>i.e.</I> the supply of one aqueduct had been accredited to another.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note109" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref109
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">109</A>
These 771 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quinariae</SPAN> are made up as follows:

