<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note110" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref110
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">110</A>
<I>i.e.</I> subject to the disposition of the Emperor.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note111" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref111
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">111</A>
The manuscript reading here is unintelligible.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note112" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref112
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">112</A>
The original <SPAN CLASS="small">MS.</SPAN> of the <I>De Aquis</I> is a hopeless confusion of figures as regards the statistics given in chapters 78‑86. The numbers, as they have come down to us in the Montecassino manuscript exhibit a great many errors, and it would be impossible to affirm what are errors, and what is the truth. Poleni endeavoured to reconcile these figures, so as to make them mathematically correct. Tables showing his adjustments, and a second set of tables, prepared by Herschel on the basis of Bücheler's figures, are given at the end of the book.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note113" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref113
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">113</A>
The manuscript reading here is hopeless except for <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">humilior</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note114" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref114
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">114</A>
The <SPAN CLASS="small">MS.</SPAN> omits the general statement usually given of 


<A ID="p411x"></A>the amount distributed for public uses, and mentions only the separate items which would fall under this general head. Poleni would insert a general statement, deriving his total from the addition of the separate amounts.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note115" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref115
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">115</A>
A branch of Marcia supplied the baths of Caracalla (built 206 <SPAN CLASS="small">A.D.</SPAN>)<SPAN CLASS="emend">.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note116" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref116
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">116</A>
The <SPAN CLASS="small">MS.</SPAN> says nothing of deliveries to private persons. Poleni, for the sake of arithmetic, would amend the text here.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify" ID="note117">
	<A CLASS="note" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref117a
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">117a</A>
	<A CLASS="note" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref117b
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">117b</A>
The <SPAN CLASS="small">MS.</SPAN> shows no gap, though a numeral is clearly called for.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note118" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref118
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">118</A>
The most important of these were the Thermae of Agrippa.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note119" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref119
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">119</A>
The name given to an artificial channel running through 


<A ID="p415x"></A>the Gardens of Agrippa on the Campus Martius and emptying into the Tiber.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note120" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref120
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">120</A>
This allusion is not clear.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note121" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref121
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">121</A>
Among them the Baths of Nero.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note122" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref122
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">122</A>
The Emperor Trajan is meant.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note123" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref123
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">123</A>
<I>e.g.</I> an artificial basin made to receive the water at its source.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note124" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref124
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">124</A>
That is, water the private right to which has become void.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note125" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref125
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">125</A>
Since censors were chosen only every five years, and held office for but eighteen months, their duties in the intervening periods devolved upon other officials.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note126" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref126
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">126</A>
Since these grants were made only for the sake of public utilities, such as baths and fulleries, and since moreover the State profited from the tax paid into the public treasury.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note127" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref127
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">127</A>
The manuscript reading has been amended as unintelligible, but the amended statement is not quite in agreement with recorded facts.
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/livy/liv.39.shtml#32
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Livy <SPAN CLASS="small">XXXIX</SPAN>.32
	</A>
says that in 185 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> it 


<A ID="p425x"></A>was certainly expected that Quintus Fabius Labeo and Lucius Porcius Licinus would be elected consuls for the next year. The elections, however, resulted otherwise: Quintus Fabius Labeo and Marcius Claudius Marcellus were consuls in 183, Lucius Porcius Licinus and Publius Claudius Pulcher in 184.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note128" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref128
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">128</A>
An eminent Roman jurist under Augustus and Tiberius.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note129" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref129
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">129</A>
The meaning of this sentence is clear, though not the construction.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note130" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref130
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">130</A>
A very large sum for those days, approximately £85.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note131" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref131
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">131</A>
The <SPAN CLASS="whole">aedile</SPAN>&shy;ship usually preceded the <SPAN CLASS="whole">consul</SPAN>&shy;ship by six years. In 33 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> Octavian was anxious that the people should be amused by shows and buildings of more than usual splendour, and Agrippa, in his loyalty to the Triumvir, descended from the rank which he had attained as a consular to serve in the inferior office of aedile.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note132" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref132
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">132</A>
Under the Republic, these special offices had been of a temporary nature; now Agrippa, and certain others following him, held this office for life.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note133" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref133
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">133</A>
In 11 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> 


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note134" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref134
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">134</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#1.23
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">23</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note135" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref135
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">135</A>
The <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">senatores pedarii</SPAN> did not enjoy full senatorial rights.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note136" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Frontinus/De_Aquis/text*.html#ref136
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">136</A>
The resolution of the senate ends at this point. The rest of the section is taken up with some comments of Frontinus on various provisions of the bill.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
